      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters characterized with uncertainty bounds and sources documented at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "All 13 primary model inputs documented with nominal values, uncertainty sources, and probability distributions. Blood viscosity modeled as normally distributed (CV 6%); inlet velocity profile uncertainty ±3%; rotational speed ±0.5%. Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainties performed across 500 samples to establish output uncertainty bounds on RH. A screening sensitivity study was also conducted to rank input contributions to output variance, confirming that rotational speed and inlet flow rate together account for approximately 78% of predicted RH variance. These screening results informed the uncertainty characterization and boundary condition selection strategy. Gradation 2 achieved."
